s:495:"<p>A course in insurance may cover the basics of the different types of 
insurance, but it could also highlight financial instruments, financial 
planning, ethical issues, public policy, microeconomics, Social Security
 and public finances. Most programs of study include assigned reading, 
class discussions, lectures, exams, research and writing. The exact area
 of study may vary based on institution and the level of the degree, 
such as bachelor’s, master’s or doctoral.<br /></p>";